Gobuster
Directory and file brute-forcing tool

Web Application
Description
Gobuster is a tool used to brute-force URIs (directories and files) in websites and DNS subdomains. It's fast and supports multiple modes for different types of enumeration.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which gobuster
Install command:

sudo apt install gobuster
Basic Syntax
gobuster dir -u <URL> -w <wordlist>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt

Directory scan - Find hidden dirs	Web enumeration	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -x php,html,txt

File extensions - Find specific files	File discovery	
gobuster dns -d target.com -w subdomains.txt

Subdomain enum - Find subdomains	DNS recon	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -o results.txt

Save output - Write results	Documentation	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -t 50

Fast scan - 50 threads	Speed up scanning	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -s "200,204,301,302,307,401"

Status codes - Show specific codes	Filter results	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -b "403,404"

Blacklist codes - Hide specific codes	Clean output	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -r

Follow redirects - Follow 301/302	Find final location	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -k

Skip SSL verify - Ignore cert errors	Self-signed certs	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -c "PHPSESSID=abc123"

With cookie - Authenticated scan	Post-login scanning	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -H "Authorization: Bearer token"

Custom header - API auth	API testing	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -a "Mozilla/5.0"

Custom User-Agent - Avoid detection	Stealth scanning	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -p http://127.0.0.1:8080

Through proxy - Route via Burp	Traffic analysis	
gobuster vhost -u http://192.168.1.1 -w vhosts.txt

Virtual host enum - Find vhosts	Multi-site servers	
gobuster dns -d target.com -w subdomains.txt -i

Show IP - Display resolved IPs	DNS mapping	
gobuster dns -d target.com -w subdomains.txt --wildcard

Wildcard detection - Handle wildcards	Wildcard DNS	
gobuster fuzz -u http://192.168.1.1/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt

Fuzz mode - Parameter fuzzing	Parameter discovery	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt --no-error

Suppress errors - Clean output	Production scans	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -n

No status - Skip status display	Script output	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -e

Expanded mode - Full URL output	Direct URL testing	
gobuster dir -u http://192.168.1.1 -w wordlist.txt -U admin -P password

Basic auth - HTTP authentication	Protected directories	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Identify target web application URL
2
Choose appropriate wordlist (common.txt for quick scan)
3
Run gobuster: gobuster dir -u <url> -w <wordlist>
4
Watch for Status 200 (found) and 301/302 (redirects)
5
Investigate interesting paths manually
6
Try with -x flag for specific file extensions
7
Save results: -o output.txt
Understanding the Output
Gobuster shows: /path (Status: 200) [Size: 1234]. Status 200 = exists, 301/302 = redirect, 403 = forbidden (exists but no access), 404 = not found.

Important Warnings
•
Directory brute forcing is noisy and easily logged
•
Only scan websites you have permission to test
•
High thread counts can overwhelm small servers
•
Some WAFs may block or rate-limit your requests
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
